# Git Branching & Timesheet App Updates

This plan covers the transition to a branching workflow and the implementation of the first set of updates from the user's task list.

## 🌳 Git Branching Workflow

We will move away from committing directly to `main`. Instead, we'll use a feature-branch approach.

1.  **Create Branch**: `git checkout -b updates-v2`
2.  **Develop**: Make changes to the code in this branch.
3.  **Local Test**: Open the local [index.html](file:///d:/AI%20Coding%20Projects/AntigravityTimesheetApp/index.html) (or use a local server) to verify changes on your computer.
4.  **Mobile Test**: 
    - We will look into [Firebase Hosting Preview Channels](https://firebase.google.com/docs/hosting/test-preview-deploy) if the app is hosted on Firebase.
    - Alternatively, we can use a local IP address to test on your phone over Wi-Fi.
5.  **GitHub Push**: `git push origin updates-v2` (keeps the work backed up in the cloud).
6.  **Merge**: Once all 15 tasks (or a logical subset) are done and tested, we'll merge `updates-v2` back into `main`.

## 🗓️ Calendar-Style PDF Invoice (v2)

### 🏗️ Proposed Architecture
We will implement **Local PDF Generation** for exact layout control.
1.  **Print View**: A hidden HTML template mirroring the manual calendar (7 columns).
2.  **Data Injection**: Each date box will show `Start-End` and `Total Hours`.
3.  **Totals**: Automatic calculation for the two pay periods (1-15, 16-End) using the updated **$26/hr** rate.
4.  **Export**: Use a client-side library to generate a perfect PDF copy.

## ⚙️ Settings: One App, Multi-User Vision

Instead of two separate apps, we will build a **single, intelligent app** that adapts to the user.

1.  **Local-Only Mode**: No accounts needed. Data is stored purely on the phone. This is for users who just want to track their own hours privately.
2.  **Pro-Sync Mode**: When a user connects their Google account, the app unlocks the automated Drive sync and Email features you currently enjoy.

### 🛠️ Configurable Variables (The Settings Menu)
- [ ] **Current Pay Rate**: Default to **$26/hr**, user-editable.
- [ ] **Your Name**: To personalize the header of the Invoice (e.g., replaces "Mitchell R Clark").
- [ ] **Employer Email**: Set the recipient for the finalized timesheets.
- [ ] **Pay Periods**: Switch between 1st-15th or standard weekly/bi-weekly cycles.
- [ ] **12hr/24hr Toggle**: Especially for the **sync_data** file (to satisfy Task #1).

## 🛠️ Proposed Changes (Revised Order)

